      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PASTOR DUNBAR (9) made it two from two when recording a resuming win last week at Bendigo, coming from a wide barrier but finishing 3.3 metres ahead of his rivals. Draws on the second line but won from there on debut. Fitter and has plenty of upside. BEAU TRUSCOTT (7) looks to have returned an improved colt having led and kept finding to score when resuming at Kilmore. Must overcome a very wide draw but could work through his grades this time in. WAR DAN PHOENIX (6) led from one spot wider when resuming and boxed on for third at Shepparton last time out. Can progress off that. CHANTILLY LASS (8) drew wider on this row and worked last start but won her only attempt at this circuit and distance so can do better.",
